    public abstract class ActivityForSearchingTumOnline<T>
extends ActivityForSearching
implements TUMOnlineRequestFetchListener, uk.co.senab.actionbarpulltorefresh.library.listeners.OnRefreshListener
    Generic class which handles all basic tasks to communicate with TUMOnline and provides a SearchView for searching the data. It implements the TUMOnlineRequestFetchListener in order to receive data from TUMOnline and implements a rich user feedback with error progress and token related layouts. Generic class parameter specifies the type of data returned by TumOnline.

      • ActivityForSearchingTumOnline

        public ActivityForSearchingTumOnline(TUMOnlineConst method,
                             java.lang.Class<T> responseType,
                             int layoutId,
                             java.lang.String auth,
                             int minLen)
        Standard constructor for ActivityForSearchingTumOnline. The given layout must include a progress_layout, failed_layout, no_token_layout and an error_layout. If the Activity should support Pull-To-Refresh it can also contain a PullToRefreshLayout named ptr_layout
        Parameters:
        method - A identifier specifying what kind of data should be fetched from TumOnline
        responseType - Class instance that identifies the response type
        layoutId - Resource id of the xml layout that should be used to inflate the activity
        auth - Authority for search suggestions declared in manifest file
        minLen - Minimum text length that has to be entered by the user before a search quest can be submitted
